    "body": "Should have added in the first post this is on Linux, openSUSE 13.2 to be exact.\n\nI have ~/.inputrc., which is commented out. There is also an /etc/inputrc. It has this:\n$if mode=vi\nset editing-mode vi\nset keymap vi\n$endif\n\nI have read that set editing-mode vi sometimes can cause issues, but opening a console and running bind -V shows, among other things, this:\n\nediting-mode is set to `emacs`\nkeymap is set to `emacs'\n\nso the vi editing mode is not set.\n\nSome playing around found that Ctr + Up arrow works as does Page Up for searching backwards through history.  I tried attaching the inputrc, but I do not the necessary permissions.\n"
  },
