    "body": "Could `readline_parse_and_bind` be set anywhere in your config? Could up and down be generating different key sequences from the ones that we set by default (`\\e[A` and `\\e[B`)? If you put these lines in `~/.inputrc`, does bash behave correctly?\n\n```\n\"\\e[A\": history-search-backward\n\"\\e[B\": history-search-forward\n```\n"
